problem:
Express as a common fraction in simplest form: $$
\sqrt{6\frac{1}{4}}
$$

response:
 To express $$
\sqrt{6\frac{1}{4}}
$$ as a common fraction in simplest form, we first convert the mixed number $$
6\frac{1}{4}
$$ to an improper fraction. The improper fraction is calculated as $$
6 \times 4 + 1 = 25
$$, so the mixed number $$
6\frac{1}{4}
$$ equals $$
\frac{25}{4}
$$ </think>

</answer>

